observations.recommendation:
Hence, we recommended that the Honorable Mayor instruct:
56. The Inventory Committee (IC) to immediately adopt the prescribed form in preparing the RPCPPE;
57. The IC to completely list and properly classify the PPEs according to its type/category;
58. That upon completion of the physical count, the General Services Office and Accounting Office undertake collaborative effort to maintain, update, and reconcile their cards and ledgers with the results of the physical count; and
59. That identified discrepancies, if any, be properly addressed by proper recognition or disposition thereof, whichever is applicable.

We recommended that the Honorable Mayor instruct the following:
4. The immediate submission of all un-submitted reports pertaining to the project namely Concreting of Park Area Access Road to Sitio Magampong the Auditor’s Office, such as the Report of Checks Issued (RCI) duly certified by the Municipal Treasurer, Report of Disbursements (ROD), disbursement vouchers, payrolls, together with its supporting documents;
5. Initiate the keeping of separate updated subsidiary records for each transfer and for future transfers from NGAs, whether or not maintained in separate bank accounts;
6. Make the necessary adjustments, if any, to correct the ledgers, trial balance, and the financial statements; and
7. Submission to the Auditor’s Office of a schedule showing all the transfers/subsidies actually received by the Management indicating the source agency, purpose, amount received, and balance, if any, as at December 31, 2021 and in the ensuing years.

We recommended and Management concurred that the concerned officials of the Treasury Office shall:
19. Faithfully prepare and accomplish their RCDs, together with its necessary abstract/schedules and supporting documents, at the end of the business day;
20. Consolidate the RCDs of all tellers;
21. Duly certify and acknowledge receipt and verification of their respective RCDs; and
22. Faithfully deposit the receipts and collections, intact, daily to avoid possible loss and misappropriation.

The Local Chief Executive shall:
50. Instruct the Inventory Committee to conduct immediately an extensive inventory of the road network system under the Municipality’s jurisdiction and prepare a report thereon;
51. Require the Municipal Accountant to religiously update the subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network based on the result of the physical count;
52. Further require the General Services Officer (GSO)/Supply Officer to religiously maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map;
53. Further require the GSO/ Supply Officer to religiously maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map; 
54. Likewise, have the GSO/Supply Officer keep an updated complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components and make a reconciliation with that of the Accounting records; and
55. Finally, require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Accountant and the General Services Office with the complete description.
